<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-02-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-02-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="658" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d658">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Jackson</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-02-21"><hi rend="italic">February 21,
                                    1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The President having accepted the honorary
                            presidency of the American committee on the Olympic games at Athens,
                            from April 22 to May 2, 1906, and the Government of Greece, through its
                            consul-general at New York, having invited this Government to be
                            officially represented on the occasion, you are, by the President’s
                            direction, hereby designated to be his representative at the games.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Elihu Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>